Kalibo is a coastal municipality in the province of Aklan. It serves as the provincial capital. The municipality has a land area of 50.75 square kilometers.
The airport is situated 2 kilometers (1.2 mi) east of the main area of Kalibo and 68 kilometers (42 mi) from Caticlan port in Malay.
